                        ܐܦܝܣܩܘܦܐ ܓܐܢܙܪܒܐ
                </span></span></h1></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns"><div class="tei-note"><span xml:lang="en" lang="en" dir="ltr">Bishop of Anazarba who received several letters from Severus.</span><span class="tei-footnote-refs" dir="ltr" lang="en" xml:lang="en"><span class="tei-footnote-ref"><a href="#bib2546-3">3</a></span> </span></div><div style="margin:0 1em 1em; color: #999999;"><small><p><span class="srp-label"><strong>Syriaca.org URI</strong></span>: <span id="syriaca-id"><a href="http://syriaca.org/person/2546">http://syriaca.org/person/2546</a></span></p></small></div></div><div xmlns:x="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" xmlns:local="http://syriaca.org/ns" class="row"><div class="col-md-8"><div class="sources"><h3>Personal Information</h3><h4>Name variant(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-listPerson">
                    <span class="tei-person">
                        <span class="tei-persName"> Entrechius, Bishop of
                                <span class="tei-placeName"> Anazarba
                            </span></span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/3045-1" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-listPerson">
                    <span class="tei-person">
                        <span class="tei-persName"> Entrechius, Bishop of
                                <span class="tei-placeName"> Anazarba
                            </span></span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/3038-1" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-listPerson">
                    <span class="tei-person">
                        <span class="tei-persName">Estorechius</span>
                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/3161-2" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Entrechius</span> was male. <a href="/3045-2" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Entrechius</span> was male. <a href="/3038-2" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Occupation(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Entrechius</span> was a bishop. <a href="/3045-3" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Entrechius</span> was Bishop of <span class="tei-placeName">Anazarba</span>. <a href="/3038-3" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Relationships</h3><p class="indent">
                            Entrechius had
                            ecclesiastical authority over Anonymous 3064 and
                                Anonymi
                                3062. <a href="/3045-11" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Theodosius
                            and Entrechius
                            had a professional relationship. <a href="/3038-18" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">Severus of
                                Antioch sent a letter to Entrechius. <a href="/3038-4" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><p class="indent">
                            Severus, Eleusinius, 
                            Soteric, and Entrechius 
                            were united in their opposition to Chalcedon.
                         <a href="/3019-9" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">
                            Severus sent a letter to
                            Entrechius discussing
                            Christology and the Incarnation.
                            
                                
                            
                         <a href="/3161-1" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Between
                                513 and 518, Severus wrote a letter to Entrechius about the
                            appointment of Anonymous
                                3064 in Rhosus. 
                                
                            
                         <a href="/3045-12" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Between
                                513 and 518, Severus wrote a letter to Entrechius bishop of Anazarba about accusations against an
                            heretical bishop.  <a href="/3038-36" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Severus
                            decided not to call on Procopius, but instead sent the presbyter
                                Theodosius to Entrechius in order
                            to examine the accusations.  <a href="/3038-38" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/><p class="indent">Severus urged
                                Entrechius
                            to work with Theodosius in order to mete out justice on the
                            ecclesiastical offenders.  <a href="/3038-41" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
